The proof of this formula is pure combinatorics: for the formula_10th order statistic to be formula_11, the number of samples that are formula_12 has to be between formula_13 and formula_14. In the case that formula_15 is the largest order statistic formula_11, there has to be formula_17 samples formula_11 (each with an independent probability of formula_19) and formula_20 samples formula_21 (each with an independent probability of formula_22). Finally there are formula_23 different ways of choosing which of the formula_24 samples are of the formula_11 kind.

The corresponding probability density function may be derived from this result, and is found to be

